This paper deals with image stitching, which is a common task in computer vision and graphics. The paper proposes a new method for content-preserving warping, which is a technique used in image stitching to deal with local misalignment caused by global homography. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and graphics (cs.GR) sub-categories. The paper also involves the use of optimization techniques to jointly estimate the colour transformation and the warped mesh vertexes, which suggests that it may also belong to the machine learning (cs.MM), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and learning (cs.LG) sub-categories.
